{0 iec_checker}

Static analysis for {{:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IEC_61131-3} IEC 61131-3}
programs. Currently supports
{{:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Structured_text} Structured Text},
{{:https://plcopen.org/technical-activities/xml-exchange} PLCOpen XML} and
{{:https://selinc.com/products/3530/} SEL XML} input formats.

The Structured Text dialect accepted by the parser is compatible with the
{{:https://github.com/sm1820/matiec} matiec} transpiler.

{1 Libraries}

The codebase is split into four public libraries. Each library has a single
top-level module that re-exports its public API.

{2 {!module-IECCheckerCore} — [iec_checker.core]}

Core data structures shared by every other component: the AST
({!module-IECCheckerCore.Syntax}), control-flow graph
({!module-IECCheckerCore.Cfg}), warning representation
({!module-IECCheckerCore.Warn}), JSON dump format
({!module-IECCheckerCore.Dump}), PLCOpen XML reader
({!module-IECCheckerCore.Plcopen}) and SEL XML reader
({!module-IECCheckerCore.Sel}).

{2 {!module-IECCheckerParser} — [iec_checker.parser]}

The lexer, Menhir grammar and source-location tracking. Turns Structured Text
text into the AST defined in {!module-IECCheckerCore.Syntax}.

{2 {!module-IECCheckerAnalysis} — [iec_checker.analysis]}

Generic semantic analyses that the rule library builds on top of:
declaration analysis ({!module-IECCheckerAnalysis.Declaration_analysis}),
use-define chains ({!module-IECCheckerAnalysis.Use_define}),
unused-variable detection ({!module-IECCheckerAnalysis.Unused_variable})
and cyclomatic-complexity scoring
({!module-IECCheckerAnalysis.Cyclomatic_complexity}).

{2 {!module-IECCheckerLib} — [iec_checker.lib]}

The actual checks. Implements the
{{:https://plcopen.org/software-construction-guidelines} PLCOpen Software
Construction Guidelines} (modules [Plcopen_cp1] … [Plcopen_cp28],
[Plcopen_l10], [Plcopen_l17], [Plcopen_n3]).
{!module-IECCheckerLib.CheckerLib} is the entry point invoked by the
[iec_checker] binary.

{1 Entry points}

- The command-line driver lives in [src/bin/iec_checker.ml] (not part of the
  documented API).
- Programmatic users should start at {!module-IECCheckerLib.CheckerLib}.
- Tools that consume the JSON IR should look at
  {!module-IECCheckerCore.Dump}.
